<subSubSection id="CE4D38BF6DFF2E5D65434DC2A7EDF102" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6E0FB98941B373DA4A128DAE08F073F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52E81A8185C8450CD23957C0A6C29F06" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
This species was originally described mainly from the Pietermaritzburg district (
<bibRefCitation id="4053168A285ADC66BBCE7DAE8D209DFE" author="Londt, JGH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="635 - 699" refId="B5" refString="Londt, JGH, 1981. Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 5. The genus Dasophrys Loew, 1858 (= Hobbyus Bromley, 1952) (Asilinae: Asilini). Annals of the Natal Museum 24 (2): 635 - 699" title="Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 5. The genus Dasophrys Loew, 1858 (= Hobbyus Bromley, 1952) (Asilinae: Asilini)." volume="24" year="1981">Londt 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D3E2F64D36C62B48787EEC463345ACC" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">A single adult male was collected in week 28.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD9A4092907CE4C489EEEDFFD87CA792" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
This distinctive species was swept from long grass. Its patterned wings are almost certainly an adaptation to forest or forest margin habitats, i.e. 
<bibRefCitation id="38845D87F832FA3302C7C5EC9DDC345C" author="Londt, JGH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="97 - 122" refId="B9" refString="Londt, JGH, 1994. Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 26. Ethological observations, and a possible ecological classification based on habitats. Annals of the Natal Museum 35: 97 - 122" title="Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 26. Ethological observations, and a possible ecological classification based on habitats." volume="35" year="1994">
<normalizedToken id="038B021E608A13EDA509CD5509DF5F5B" originalValue="Londt’s">Londt's</normalizedToken>
(1994)
</bibRefCitation>
ecological category 5b (within shrubs and bushes) and so the Jacana specimen was certainly out of its previously recorded 
<normalizedToken id="05D50EB1904A484AD15010D199637E2D" originalValue="‘preferred’">'preferred'</normalizedToken>
habitat.
</paragraph>
